metadata.name: Glomularus Unleashed #32
metadata.description:
'Glomularus Unleashed' is a limited edition drop, in appreciation of passionate and generous supporters. 

The project continues my explorations in artificial life, moving Glomularus outside of the computational void and into the world at large. 'Glomularus Unleashed' includes 23 unique immersive environments. 



Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
1-9: add acceleration
-, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
f, g: reduce | increase fog
p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite 'Glomularus Unleashed' screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: CASCADE #83
metadata.description:
‚ÄòCASCADE‚Äô is an animated and interactive art series created with javascript by the collaborative efforts of Jos√© Gasparian and MCHX. The series is inspired by the captivating beauty of water, a source of fascination for both artists and it features two distinctive palettes, each created by one of the artists. 

The endless real time animation captures the essence of water, its ever-changing form, and the interplay of light and shadow. It creates a sense of movement and dynamism, immersing the viewer in a world of fluidity and serene beauty.

Each token has an original set of characteristics, randomly determined by the hash from the following options:

‚Ä¢ Color palettes (JG or MCHX)
‚Ä¢ Animation speed (Ocean, River or Waterfall) and direction (North or South)
‚Ä¢ Number of cascades (1, 2, 3 or 4)
‚Ä¢ Number of color sets (2, 4, 7 or 13)

Don't forget to click on the canvas to change the color combinations! We hope you enjoy it! üôÇ

JG & MCHX. 2023.

metadata.name: Ruins #72
metadata.description:
Ruins is a generative art project depicting abandoned ruins in a wild and beautiful environment where nature has taken over.

The soothing and hypnotic animation of the sky can be controlled by:
- clicking to pause or resume animation
- double-clicking to pause and display the initial image
- repeatedly pressing the + or - keys (or directional keys) to speed up or slow down the animation
- pressing f to increase the refresh rate to 60 FPS

metadata.name: Punktwelt #116
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a png. Press ‚Äô4‚Äô to export a high resolution png. Press ‚Äô8‚Äô to export a very high resolution png. Press ‚Äôe‚Äô to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Departure Within Shattered Windmills #390
metadata.description:
I wrote the following when reviewing the outputs...

The wind is gone,
My windmill falls,
I reach out to catch the pieces.
Half fall in my right hand,
The others in my left,
Two stacks of colored paper.
I‚Äôm holding my windmill,
I feel the breeze in my hair.
Each hand is empty,
My windmill rises,
I can see the wind.

'Departure Within Shattered Windmills' was originally inspired by suprematism, and then started to gain more complexity. It is still a combination of simple features, subdivided quads drawn on different planes of perspective. Chaos simulated by many organized grids. Countless pieces of a windmill.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Time #13
metadata.description:
To pass time while in meetings or just trying to solve a problem I like to sketch on my notebook continuous abstract lines, usually following a short pattern without paying too much attention to the process. 

In this project I take this to the extreme in a generative approach. The resulting image is one continuous line imperfectly repeating the same pattern for a minute. You can travel back in time and zoom in to explore all layers.

Instructions:

- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 't' to switch time travel mode (use your mouse to go back in time)
- press 'p' in 'Open live' to download the current view it in a custom resolution. This usually results in better quality for prints.

Berlin, January 2022
@bgola
